<li><cite id="endnote_devlin" style="font-style: normal;"><a href="#ref_devlin" title=""><b>^</b></a></cite>&#160; Kate Devlin, Alan Chalmers, Alexander Wilkie, Werner Purgathofer. "STAR Report on Tone Reproduction and Physically Based Spectral Rendering" in <a href="/wiki/Eurographics" title="Eurographics">Eurographics</a> 2002. <a href="/wiki/Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">DOI</a>: <a href="http://doi.acm.org/10.1145/1073204.1073242" class="external text" title="http://doi.acm.org/10.1145/1073204.1073242" rel="nofollow">10.1145/1073204.1073242</a></li>
<li><cite id="endnote_fattal" style="font-style: normal;"><a href="#ref_fattal" title=""><b>^</b></a></cite>&#160; Raanan Fattal, Dani Lischinski, Michael Werman. <a href="http://www.cs.huji.ac.il/~danix/hdr/" class="external text" title="http://www.cs.huji.ac.il/~danix/hdr/" rel="nofollow">"Gradient Domain High Dynamic Range Compression"</a></li>
<li><cite id="endnote_mantiuk" style="font-style: normal;"><a href="#ref_mantiuk" title=""><b>^</b></a></cite>&#160; Rafal Mantiuk, Karol Myszkowski, Hans-Peter Seidel. <a href="http://www.mpi-sb.mpg.de/~mantiuk/contrast_domain/" class="external text" title="http://www.mpi-sb.mpg.de/~mantiuk/contrast_domain/" rel="nofollow">"A Perceptual Framework for Contrast Processing of High Dynamic Range Images"</a></li>
<li><cite id="endnote_gilchrist" style="font-style: normal;"><a href="#ref_gilchrist" title=""><b>^</b></a></cite>&#160; Alan Gilchrist. <a href="http://psychology.rutgers.edu/~alan/theory3/" class="external text" title="http://psychology.rutgers.edu/~alan/theory3/" rel="nofollow">"An Anchoring Theory of Lightness Perception"</a>.</li>
<li><cite id="endnote_krawczyk" style="font-style: normal;"><a href="#ref_krawczyk" title=""><b>^</b></a></cite>&#160; Grzegorz Krawczyk, Karol Myszkowski, Hans-Peter Seidel. <a href="http://www.mpi-inf.mpg.de/resources/hdr/lightness/" class="external text" title="http://www.mpi-inf.mpg.de/resources/hdr/lightness/" rel="nofollow">"Lightness Perception in Tone Reproduction for High Dynamic Range Images"</a></li>
</ol>
